name: beverage carton converting | beverage carton converting | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/28984/documentation

This dataset represents the production of 1000 square meters of beverage carton from liquid packaging board (LPB), LDPE granulate and aluminium foil. Data are based on the average production process of the main European beverage carton producers.;;;;;The dataset is broadly applicable for converting of carton based liquid packaging material, and not specific to any particular beverage package format or family. ;The inventory does not list preset inputs of liquid packaging board, polyethylene, aluminium or any other raw materials that can be used in beverage carton packaging material. These data should be specified by the user according to the particular package of interest.; 

From the reception of LPB, polyethylene granulate and aluminium foil from the factory gate.

This activity ends with the packaging of the produced beverage cartons before loading the products on lorries. The dataset includes  the steps of cutting, laminating, folding and printing and packaging.The dataset does not include production of machinery/infrastructure.
category: C:Manufacturing/17:Manufacture of paper and paper products/170:Manufacture of paper and paper products/1702:Manufacture of corrugated paper and paperboard and of containers of paper a

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Average data from the three main European converters collected from 20 European sites (situated in Spain, Germany, Hungary, France, Serbia, Ukraine, Sweden, Netherlands, Russia, Italy, UK, Denmark and Finland) weighted according to production volumes. European production can be considered as representative for global geography.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Production of beverage cartons from liquid packaging board, polyethylene granulate and aluminiuim foil. Process steps include cutting of LPB and aluminium foil, melting of PE granualte, laminating to compund and printing of compaund. ;Average of the used technology across Europe
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: weighted average (production volume)  from 20 European sites
